@page "/reference"

<PageTitle>Theme tokens</PageTitle>

<h1>Theme tokens</h1>
<p class="lead">
    The Just the Docs translation uses a small set of tokens to keep pages consistent.
    Update them in <code>styles/app.scss</code>.
</p>

<h2>Color palette</h2>
<table>
    <thead>
    <tr>
        <th>Token</th>
        <th>Usage</th>
        <th>Hex</th>
    </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
    <tr>
        <td>Accent</td>
        <td>Links, buttons, active nav</td>
        <td>#2f5bcc</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Surface</td>
        <td>Cards, panels, content background</td>
        <td>#ffffff</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Border</td>
        <td>Hairline separators</td>
        <td>#e2e6ee</td>
    </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<h2>Reusable classes</h2>
<ul class="key-list">
    <li><code>.callout</code> for notes and warnings.</li>
    <li><code>.card-grid</code> to display linked content.</li>
    <li><code>.steps</code> for short ordered instructions.</li>
</ul>

<blockquote>
    The theme is optimized for documentation pages first. Use the same building blocks
    across new calculators to keep everything consistent.
</blockquote>
